The paper is about large scale retrieval systems and proposes a unified framework for predicting performance-sensitive parameters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses machine learning techniques for predicting these parameters, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses efficiency and effectiveness trade-offs, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of the framework in large scale search systems, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
